<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,937,1975]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,468,1012,1037]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
The species belongs in the 
<taxonomicName box="[793,868,1013,1036]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Beardius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parcus">
<emphasis box="[793,868,1013,1036]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">parcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The male can be separated from all other members of the genus by the combination of the following characters: acrostichals present; superior volsella leafshaped; and inferior volsella lacking projection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,937,1975]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1119,1144]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name refers to the 
<typeStatus box="[609,657,1120,1144]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">type</typeStatus>
locality, Sapiranga Reserve, 
<collectingRegion box="[990,1059,1119,1144]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Bahia</collectingRegion>
. The name is to be regarded as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,937,1975]" box="[151,282,1191,1216]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,937,1975]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1228,1253]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Male</emphasis>
(n = 1). Total length 
<quantity box="[514,620,1228,1253]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.16" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="2.16">2.16 mm</quantity>
. Wing length 
<quantity box="[784,889,1228,1253]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" unit="mm" value="1.15">1.15 mm</quantity>
. Total length / wing length 2.15. Wing length / length of profemur 1.89.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,937,1975]" box="[199,1436,1300,1325]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[199,329,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Coloration.</emphasis>
Head and thorax pale; abdomen pale with large, anterior brown band on tergites II–VIII. Legs pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,937,1975]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[199,267,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Head.</emphasis>
AR 1.14, ultimate flagellomere 487 µm long. Inner verticals 3, outer verticals 2, postorbitals 4. Clypeus with 10 setae. Tentorium 71 µm long, 30 µm wide. Stipes 106 µm long. Palpomere lengths (in µm): 25, 20, 71, 83, 104. Third palpomere with 3 sensillae subapically, longest 15 µm long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,937,1975]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Thorax</emphasis>
. Scutal tubercle absent. Dorsocentrals 9, 2 of them close to antepronotum; acrostichals 8; prealars 3. Scutellum with 6 setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,937,1975]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[199,258,1517,1540]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[273,372,1516,1541]" captionStart="FIGURES 112–114" captionStartId="61.[151,264,1497,1519]" captionTargetBox="[277,1315,213,1462]" captionTargetId="figure-182@61.[253,1333,177,1500]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES 112–114. Beardius sapiranga sp. n., male. 112—wing; 113—tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 114—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5270966" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5270966/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 112</figureCitation>
). VR 1.26. R with 5 setae, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[702,710,1531,1545]" fontSize="6" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">1</subScript>
with 1 seta, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[877,901,1531,1545]" fontSize="6" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">4+5</subScript>
with 2 setae at apex. Brachiolum with 2 setae. Remaining veins bare.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,937,1975]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[199,252,1592,1615]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Legs</emphasis>
. Spur of fore tibia (including scale) 46 µm long, spur of mid tibia (including comb) 58 µm long, spur of hind tibia (including comb) 66 µm long. Width at apex of fore tibia 38 µm, of mid tibia 38 µm, of hind tibia 43 µm. Lengths and proportions of legs as in 
<tableCitation box="[573,673,1662,1687]" captionStart="TABLE 20" captionStartId="60.[151,239,563,586]" captionText="TABLE 20. Lengths (in µm) and proportions of legs of Beardius sapiranga sp. n., male (n = 1)." pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Table 20</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,937,1975]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis box="[199,342,1699,1722]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[359,518,1698,1723]" captionStart="FIGURES 112–114" captionStartId="61.[151,264,1497,1519]" captionTargetBox="[277,1315,213,1462]" captionTargetId="figure-182@61.[253,1333,177,1500]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURES 112–114. Beardius sapiranga sp. n., male. 112—wing; 113—tergite IX and dorsal aspect of left gonocoxite and gonostylus; 114—hypopygium with anal point and tergite IX removed, left dorsal aspect, right ventral aspect." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5270966" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5270966/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Figs 113–114</figureCitation>
). Anal point absent. Tergite IX without setae, tergal bands absent. Laterosternite IX with 1 seta. Phallapodeme 63 µm long. Transverse sternapodeme 33 µm long. Gonocoxite 127 µm long. Superior volsella leaf-shaped, 61 µm long, with 9 dorsal, 2 apical, and 2 ventral setae, covered with microtrichia in basal 2/3. Median volsella 5 µm long, with 2 apical setae, longest 20 µm long. Inferior volsella clavate, curved, 63 µm long, with 2 apical thin and 5 subapical stout, bifid setae; projection absent. Gonostylus 106 µm long. HR 1.19. HV 2.52.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1436,937,1975]" box="[199,606,1914,1939]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,481,1914,1939]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Female and immatures.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
